This is a description of the *INFS 3087 Advanced Topics in Data Science* course. The course is designed to provide students with advanced knowledge in various data science fields, focusing on responsible AI, time series analysis, computer vision, and natural language processing.

# Course Structure

The course is structured over a 10-week period. Each week contains 8-10 hours of study materials, including readings, multimedia presentations, and learning activities. Students are expected to dedicate approximately 15 hours per week to cover the study materials, assessments, and independent learning.

# Course Schedule

| Week | Topic                                                 | Assessment                              |
|------|-------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------|
| 1    | Introduction to Responsible AI                        |                                         |
| 2    | Principles of Responsible AI                          |                                         |
| 3    | Time Series Analysis                                  | Assessment 2a - Project Part 1          |
| 4    | Time Series Forecasting                               |                                         |
| 5    | Introduction to Computer Vision                       |                                         |
| 6    | Object Detection and Localisation in Computer Vision  | Assessment 1a - Continuous Assessment   |
| 7    | Deep Learning and Machine Learning in Computer Vision |                                         |
| 8    | Natural Language Processing                           | Assessment 1b - Continuous Assessment   |
| 9    | Language Generation Models                            |                                         |
| 10   | Language Generation Model and Ethics                  | Assessment 2b - Project Part 2          |

# Study Plan Guidelines

Students should divide their time between course content, learning activities, assessments, and independent study. Flexibility is offered to allow students to work through the course at their own pace.
